  h3 Tough Losses
  p After a season of preparation and anticipation, nothing dampens the mood of A/E Weekend like a loss to Exeter.
  p &ldquo;All I remember was it was bitterly cold and they were beating us so badly that near the end they let me get into the game as a quarterback, and my ankles were practically frozen. The ground was frozen. Your cleats couldn&rsquo;t even get in there. It was really, besides losing so badly, a bitterly cold day,&rdquo; said Bassett.
  
