  p &ldquo;We had a poor season leading up to the Exeter game. But that was a big event, not just the Andover/Exeter game, but that was my first year at Andover. And that game was so bitterly cold, the other three games were much more pleasant weather. Oh god, was it cold. All I remember. I don&rsquo;t think I played a game that was that cold ever. Anywhere, in college, or anywhere,&rdquo; said Bassett. He and Bamford overlapped at Andover for two years in the 1950s.
  p In such a tense rivalry, a loss like the one Andover sustained in 1956 is devastating. But the cold – and the loss – did not linger for long.
